## AI Assistant Guidelines

### What AI Should Do

- Use CoreUI React PRO components and existing project patterns.
- Follow the App Router structure already present in `src/app`.
- Keep documentation/demo pages consistent with neighboring pages.
- Update route files and sidebar config together when needed.
- Add concise JSDoc when introducing important new modules or architectural changes.
- Respect static export constraints and hydration concerns.
- Prefer adapting nearby code over inventing a parallel pattern.

### What AI Should Not Do

- Do not introduce alternative UI libraries.
- Do not rewrite App Router structure into a React Router mental model.
- Do not add unnecessary global CSS for a narrow demo need.
- Do not use `next/image` blindly in export mode.
- Do not place layout-wide logic directly in random feature pages.
- Do not expand Redux usage for simple local state.
- Do not ignore the difference between `(views)` and `(pages)` route groups.

